# GitHub Actions version standard (BimRoss)

When editing workflow files, keep action versions aligned to a clear default so we do not drift into deprecated runtimes.

## Default policy

- Prefer the **latest supported major** for first-party actions (`actions/*`) and core Docker actions (`docker/*`) used in this workspace.
- If the workspace is intentionally mid-rollout, match the **current workspace majority major** first, then schedule the major bump explicitly.
- If there is a conflict between "workspace majority" and an active deprecation warning (for example Node runtime deprecations), prefer the **latest supported major**.

## Required checks on workflow edits

1. Scan current usage in target workflow(s) and nearby canonical repos.
2. Upgrade majors that are behind and still supported.
3. Re-run CI for the changed workflow and verify success.
4. Record any intentional exception in the PR/commit note.

## Practical baseline (current BimRoss standard)

- `actions/checkout@v6`
- `actions/setup-go@v6`
- `docker/setup-buildx-action@v4`
- `docker/login-action@v4`
- `docker/metadata-action@v6`
- `docker/build-push-action@v7`

If an action has no newer stable major yet, stay on the newest stable minor/patch within that major.

## Validation commands

```bash
rg "uses:\\s+(actions|docker)/" .github/workflows
gh run list --limit 10
gh run watch <run-id> --exit-status
```
